erstood to be associated with political opposition, have been central to the reworking of political identities and legitimacy bids across the political spectrum. Norén-Nilsson examines the entanglement of notions of democracy and national identity and traces out a tension between domestic elite imaginings and the liberal democratic framework in which they operate  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Apr 2019) 0aElectionszCambodia. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501725944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501725944.jpg  a978-3-11-066749-3  COR eBook-Package 2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles